newsitem.title: USA: U.S. bulk millfeeds - Prices mixed in quiet market.
newsitem.headline: U.S. bulk millfeeds - Prices mixed in quiet market.

text.p: Millfeed prices were mixed on Wednesday as many dealers kept a close watch on declining CBOT corn prices.
"Business has died," one dealer said. He said many buyers were on the sidelines waiting for lower millfeed prices. "There appears to be an easiness, mainly because of the grain markets," he said.
A Tennessee dealer agreed, noting that the nearby positions were soft with pressure from the CBOT board.
A Missouri broker said demand has also slackened for millfeed pellets for catfish.
"The cool weather has slowed down their metabolism and catfish (in Mississippi ponds) do not eat as much," he said.
On the other hand, one Minnesota dealer said nearby supplies remained very tight.
"People call me everyday for immediate shipments," he said. "Supplies are not adequate."
He said some areas are out of old crop corn and have not started harvesting.
